{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-16T22:04:15.762Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1776377055762_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-025@20260416T054258Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-16\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/operator_diagnostics.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/glyphweave/scenes.py`\n- `tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py`\n- `specs/t-025@20260416t054258z-spec.md`\n- `ESCALATIONS.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation accurately reflects the requirements in the specification. `OperatorDiagnostics` now includes `production_course`, `theramini_relation`, and `critique_notes`. These fields are populated with appropriate fallbacks from `scene_metadata`, `score_tree`, and `composer_state`. The `CypherClawArt.status_display` correctly renders these new fields.\n\n## Completeness\nAll acceptance criteria are met:\n- `production_course`, `theramini_relation`, and `critique_notes` are visible in the status output.\n- Diagnostics degrade gracefully to \"unavailable\" when data is absent.\n- Tests verify the status payload shape and ensure no hallucinated fields.\n- Full validation suite (pytest, ruff, mypy) passes.\n\n## Consistency\nThe new diagnostics follow the established pattern of reading authority files and providing compact status strings. The use of `_label()` ensures that internal underscores are replaced with spaces for human-readable output, maintaining UI consistency.\n\n## Security\nNo security issues were identified. File reading is handled safely through `_read_json` with comprehensive exception handling. No secrets or sensitive data are exposed.\n\n## Quality\nThe code quality is high, with clear separation of concerns and robust error handling. The test suite is comprehensive, covering edge cases like missing or corrupt authority files and ensuring fallback logic works as intended.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid. The fallback logic for `production_course` and `theramini_relation` is well-structured. The decision to derive `critique_notes` from `ear_metrics` avoids the need for a new authority file while still providing valuable feedback to the operator.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-025@20260416t054258z-verify.md"}}
